OL,3,CCouncils warn SEND deficits mean they
OL,4,Ccould go bankrupt 'overnight'
OL,6,FLarge and often rural councils
OL,7,Frepresented by the CCN have the
OL,8,Flargest deficits. This year #2 billion
OL,9,F- or half of the total deficit - falls
OL,10,Fon the shoulders of its 38 members who
OL,11,Fsay the situation is now
OL,12,F"unmanageable". Their deficits are
OL,13,Fexpected to rise to #2.7 billion in
OL,14,F2025/26, and then #3.8 billion.
OL,16,FThe councils have only been able to
OL,17,Fcarry the deficits because the
OL,18,Fgovernment introduced an accounting
OL,19,Fmethod known as a 'statutory override'
OL,20,Fthat keeps the money off the books,
OL,21,Fbut it is due to expire in March 2026.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G3/9
